cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object tracking and segmentation in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework that combines online multiple target tracking and segmentation, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also uses structured learning and network flow, which are common in machine learning and optimization, further supporting cs.AI. The paper also mentions the use of Conditional Random Field (CRF), which is a probabilistic graphical model, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. The paper also deals with video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also mentions difficulties in multiple target tracking, which involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible category.
